<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="291" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1826,2068]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="291" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,203,1826,1852]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Notes</emphasis>
: This species was described by Thomas 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, T." box="[657,849,1826,1853]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="425 - 526" refId="ref3649" refString="Anderson, T. (1867) An Enumeration of the Indian Species of Acanthaceae. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 9: 425 - 526. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1867. tb 01308. x" type="journal article" year="1867">Anderson (1867)</bibRefCitation>
, who cited two different gatherings in the protologue, viz. ‘in collibus Babadoodun, Law’ [on the hills of Babadoodun (Baba Budan), collected by 
<collectorName box="[1191,1244,1861,1888]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Law</collectorName>
] and ‘in montibus Concan et Malabar, Stocks, Law [in the mountains of Konkan and Malabar collected by 
<collectorName box="[1139,1214,1898,1924]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Stocks</collectorName>
and Law], these two gatherings must be treated as 
<typeStatus box="[456,554,1934,1960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">syntypes</typeStatus>
(Art. 9.6 of the ICN). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R." box="[793,1136,1934,1960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" pagination="81 - 130" refId="ref4246" refString="Shendage, S. M. &amp; Yadav, S. R. (2010) Revision of the genus Barleria (Acanthaceae) in India. Rheedea 20: 81 - 130." type="journal article" year="2010">Shendage &amp; Yadav (2010: 103)</bibRefCitation>
indicated “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1258,1321,1934,1960]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1329,1447,1934,1960]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0388E565072EA23553D2EF35FA394FED:8EFE02A8072EA23653D2EEF6FE5548FD" box="[136,372,1970,1996]" country="India" name="Chikmagalur district" pageId="5" pageNumber="290" stateProvince="Karnataka">Chikmagalur district</location>
, Bababudan hills, 
<emphasis box="[581,739,1970,1996]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Stocks &amp; Law</emphasis>
33 (CAL)” as the type, again failing to satisfy Art. 7.11 of the ICN so their type indication has no standing. We select the specimen from Anderson’s Herbarium collected by 
<collectorName box="[1402,1452,2006,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Law</collectorName>
(CAL0000019892) (
<figureCitation box="[366,433,2042,2068]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[190,1398,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Barleria lawii (CAL0000019892) [Reproduced with kind permission of The Director, Botanical Survey of India, Kolkata.]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577576/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). From Bababoodun [Baba Budan] as 
<typeStatus box="[862,965,2042,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="290">lectotype</typeStatus>
as it matches well with the protologue. The other 
<typeStatus box="[200,287,159,185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">syntype</typeStatus>
gathering, 
<emphasis box="[412,600,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">
<collectorName box="[412,484,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Stocks</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[517,565,159,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="291">Law</collectorName>
33
</emphasis>
, from the Hooker et Thomson Herbarium is represented in BR (no. 694246), C (C10004759), CAL (CAL0000019891), and P (P00719485, P00719488, P00719487 and P00719490).
</paragraph>
